  "result": {
    "markdown": "---\ntitle: \"Data Analysis: Simulated Experiments\"\nsubtitle: \"Use these Apps to develop data skills\"\nauthor: \"Pedro J. Aphalo\"\ndate: \"2023-07-02\"\nformat:\n  html:\n    code-fold: true\n    code-tools: true\nruntime: shiny\n---\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n:::\n\n\n## Introduction\n\n- Data analysis is not an exact science\n- It involves developing skills, such as \"reading\" plots.\n- We will use interactive Apps to visualize the effect of replication and variability. \n- In the apps, data are simulated by drawing (pseudo-)random samples from the Normal distribution.\n\n::: callout-hint\nThis page collects several Shiny + R Apps that aim at helping those new to data\nanalaysis to start developing these skills. They provide a tasting of what\nskills support data analysis. Of course, they are no substitute for practice in\nanalysing true rather than simulated data. Neither there is a substitute to\nmultiple starts at analysing data and extracting information from them.\n:::\n\n## How do sampled data look as population parameters change?\n\nIn this App:\n\n- The mean of the Control distribution is kept at zero.\n- You can choose the value of the mean for Treatment.\n- You can choose the value of the standard deviation used.\n- You can choose the size of samples ($\\approx$ number of replicates).\n- The plot shows: simulated observations as rug plots on the $x$ axis, _sample_ \n  \"empirical\" distributions and the _population_ means as blue vertical dotted lines.\n- **To do:** Run the simulation multiple times for each set of values you set for the\n  population parameters.\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div class=\"shiny-input-panel\">\n<div class=\"shiny-flow-layout\">\n<div>\n<div class=\"form-group shiny-input-container\">\n<label class=\"control-label\" id=\"mean_treat-label\" for=\"mean_treat\">Mean of 'Treatment':</label>\n<div>\n<select id=\"mean_treat\"><option value=\"0.001\">0.001</option>\n<option value=\"0.01\">0.01</option>\n<option value=\"0.1\">0.1</option>\n<option value=\"1\">1</option>\n<option value=\"10\" selected>10</option>\n<option value=\"100\">100</option></select>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"mean_treat\" data-nonempty=\"\">{\"plugins\":[\"selectize-plugin-a11y\"]}</script>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div class=\"form-group shiny-input-container\">\n<label class=\"control-label\" id=\"n_replicates-label\" for=\"n_replicates\">Number of replicates:</label>\n<div>\n<select id=\"n_replicates\"><option value=\"10\">10</option>\n<option value=\"20\">20</option>\n<option value=\"40\">40</option>\n<option value=\"100\" selected>100</option>\n<option value=\"1000\">1000</option>\n<option value=\"10000\">10000</option></select>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"n_replicates\" data-nonempty=\"\">{\"plugins\":[\"selectize-plugin-a11y\"]}</script>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div class=\"form-group shiny-input-container\">\n<label class=\"control-label\" id=\"sd_adjust-label\" for=\"sd_adjust\">Standard deviation:</label>\n<input class=\"js-range-slider\" id=\"sd_adjust\" data-skin=\"shiny\" data-min=\"0\" data-max=\"10\" data-from=\"1\" data-step=\"0.2\" data-grid=\"true\" data-grid-num=\"10\" data-grid-snap=\"false\" data-prettify-separator=\",\" data-prettify-enabled=\"true\" data-keyboard=\"true\" data-data-type=\"number\"/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<button id=\"refresh\" type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-default action-button\">New simulation</button>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n```\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div class=\"shiny-plot-output html-fill-item\" id=\"out24374c2dafb30af2\" style=\"width:100%;height:400px;\"></div>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n\n## Sample summaries (mean and standard deviation)\n\n- **To do:** For each condition run **15** or more simulations.\n    * observe how the sample mean and sd change when you:\n- Keep constant the standard deviation of the populations sampled\n    * and change the Treatment effect size.\n- Keep the Treatment effect size constant\n    * and change the standard deviation of the populations sampled.\n- Keep the Treatment effect size and the standard deviation constant\n    * and change number of replicates.\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div class=\"shiny-input-panel\">\n<div class=\"shiny-flow-layout\">\n<div>\n<div class=\"form-group shiny-input-container\">\n<label class=\"control-label\" id=\"mean_treat1-label\" for=\"mean_treat1\">Mean of 'Treatment':</label>\n<div>\n<select id=\"mean_treat1\"><option value=\"0.001\">0.001</option>\n<option value=\"0.01\">0.01</option>\n<option value=\"0.1\">0.1</option>\n<option value=\"1\" selected>1</option>\n<option value=\"10\">10</option>\n<option value=\"100\">100</option></select>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"mean_treat1\" data-nonempty=\"\">{\"plugins\":[\"selectize-plugin-a11y\"]}</script>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div class=\"form-group shiny-input-container\">\n<label class=\"control-label\" id=\"n_replicates1-label\" for=\"n_replicates1\">Number of replicates:</label>\n<div>\n<select id=\"n_replicates1\"><option value=\"3\">3</option>\n<option value=\"5\">5</option>\n<option value=\"10\" selected>10</option>\n<option value=\"20\">20</option>\n<option value=\"40\">40</option>\n<option value=\"100\">100</option>\n<option value=\"1000\">1000</option>\n<option value=\"10000\">10000</option></select>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"n_replicates1\" data-nonempty=\"\">{\"plugins\":[\"selectize-plugin-a11y\"]}</script>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div class=\"form-group shiny-input-container\">\n<label class=\"control-label\" id=\"sd_adjust1-label\" for=\"sd_adjust1\">Standard deviation:</label>\n<input class=\"js-range-slider\" id=\"sd_adjust1\" data-skin=\"shiny\" data-min=\"0\" data-max=\"10\" data-from=\"1\" data-step=\"0.2\" data-grid=\"true\" data-grid-num=\"10\" data-grid-snap=\"false\" data-prettify-separator=\",\" data-prettify-enabled=\"true\" data-keyboard=\"true\" data-data-type=\"number\"/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div class=\"form-group shiny-input-container\">\n<div class=\"checkbox\">\n<label>\n<input id=\"disp_ttest\" type=\"checkbox\"/>\n<span>t-test</span>\n</label>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<button id=\"refresh1\" type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-default action-button\">New simulation</button>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n```\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<pre class=\"shiny-text-output noplaceholder\" id=\"out844425c2eec32953\"></pre>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n\n## Simulation experiment: ANOVA\n\n- **To do:** For each condition run **15** or more simulations.\n    * consider if a non-significant _p_-value demonstrate lack of treatment effect or not.\n- Keep the Treatment effect size constant.\n    * change number of replicates and see how this affects the _p_-value and the plotted standard error.\n- Keep the Treatment effect size constant.\n    * change the standard deviation of the populations sampled.\n    \n- What can you conclude from a significant _p_-value?\n- Can you conclude something more than \"significant effect\"?\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div class=\"shiny-input-panel\">\n<div class=\"shiny-flow-layout\">\n<div>\n<div class=\"form-group shiny-input-container\">\n<label class=\"control-label\" id=\"mean_treat2-label\" for=\"mean_treat2\">Mean of 'Treatment':</label>\n<div>\n<select id=\"mean_treat2\"><option value=\"0.001\">0.001</option>\n<option value=\"0.01\">0.01</option>\n<option value=\"0.1\">0.1</option>\n<option value=\"1\" selected>1</option>\n<option value=\"10\">10</option>\n<option value=\"100\">100</option></select>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"mean_treat2\" data-nonempty=\"\">{\"plugins\":[\"selectize-plugin-a11y\"]}</script>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div class=\"form-group shiny-input-container\">\n<label class=\"control-label\" id=\"n_replicates2-label\" for=\"n_replicates2\">Number of replicates:</label>\n<div>\n<select id=\"n_replicates2\"><option value=\"3\">3</option>\n<option value=\"5\">5</option>\n<option value=\"10\" selected>10</option>\n<option value=\"20\">20</option>\n<option value=\"40\">40</option>\n<option value=\"100\">100</option>\n<option value=\"1000\">1000</option>\n<option value=\"10000\">10000</option></select>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"n_replicates2\" data-nonempty=\"\">{\"plugins\":[\"selectize-plugin-a11y\"]}</script>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div class=\"form-group shiny-input-container\">\n<label class=\"control-label\" id=\"sd_adjust2-label\" for=\"sd_adjust2\">Standard deviation:</label>\n<input class=\"js-range-slider\" id=\"sd_adjust2\" data-skin=\"shiny\" data-min=\"0\" data-max=\"10\" data-from=\"1\" data-step=\"0.2\" data-grid=\"true\" data-grid-num=\"10\" data-grid-snap=\"false\" data-prettify-separator=\",\" data-prettify-enabled=\"true\" data-keyboard=\"true\" data-data-type=\"number\"/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<button id=\"refresh2\" type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-default action-button\">New simulation</button>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n```\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div class=\"shiny-plot-output html-fill-item\" id=\"outc70750aae71ffb9c\" style=\"width:100%;height:400px;\"></div>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n\n## Simulation experiment: linear regression\n\n- **To do:** For each condition run **15** or more simulations.\n    * observe how statistical significance and $R^2$ very when you:\n- Keep constant the standard deviation of the populations sampled.\n    * change the slope size.\n    * change the intercept size.\n- Keep the slope size constant.\n    * change the standard deviation of the populations sampled.\n- Keep the Treatment effect size and the standard deviation constant.\n    * change number of replicates.\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-4\">\n<form class=\"well\" role=\"complementary\">\n<div class=\"form-group shiny-input-container\">\n<label class=\"control-label\" id=\"num_intercept4-label\" for=\"num_intercept4\">Intercept:</label>\n<div>\n<select id=\"num_intercept4\"><option value=\"-1\">-1</option>\n<option value=\"-0.1\">-0.1</option>\n<option value=\"0\" selected>0</option>\n<option value=\"0.1\">0.1</option>\n<option value=\"1\">1</option></select>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"num_intercept4\" data-nonempty=\"\">{\"plugins\":[\"selectize-plugin-a11y\"]}</script>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"form-group shiny-input-container\">\n<label class=\"control-label\" id=\"num_slope4-label\" for=\"num_slope4\">Slope of resp. to x:</label>\n<div>\n<select id=\"num_slope4\"><option value=\"-1\">-1</option>\n<option value=\"-0.1\">-0.1</option>\n<option value=\"0\">0</option>\n<option value=\"0.1\" selected>0.1</option>\n<option value=\"1\">1</option></select>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"num_slope4\" data-nonempty=\"\">{\"plugins\":[\"selectize-plugin-a11y\"]}</script>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"form-group shiny-input-container\">\n<label class=\"control-label\" id=\"num_observations4-label\" for=\"num_observations4\">n data:</label>\n<div>\n<select id=\"num_observations4\"><option value=\"5\">5</option>\n<option value=\"10\">10</option>\n<option value=\"25\">25</option>\n<option value=\"50\">50</option>\n<option value=\"100\" selected>100</option>\n<option value=\"1000\">1000</option>\n<option value=\"10000\">10000</option></select>\n<script type=\"application/json\" data-for=\"num_observations4\" data-nonempty=\"\">{\"plugins\":[\"selectize-plugin-a11y\"]}</script>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"form-group shiny-input-container\">\n<label class=\"control-label\" id=\"sd_adjust4-label\" for=\"sd_adjust4\">s.d.:</label>\n<input class=\"js-range-slider\" id=\"sd_adjust4\" data-skin=\"shiny\" data-min=\"0\" data-max=\"10\" data-from=\"1\" data-step=\"0.2\" data-grid=\"true\" data-grid-num=\"10\" data-grid-snap=\"false\" data-prettify-separator=\",\" data-prettify-enabled=\"true\" data-keyboard=\"true\" data-data-type=\"number\"/>\n</div>\n<div class=\"form-group shiny-input-container\">\n<div class=\"checkbox\">\n<label>\n<input id=\"disp_equation4\" type=\"checkbox\" checked=\"checked\"/>\n<span>Equation</span>\n</label>\n</div>\n</div>\n<button id=\"refresh4\" type=\"button\" class=\"btn btn-default action-button\">New simulation</button>\n</form>\n</div>\n<div class=\"col-sm-8\" role=\"main\">\n<div class=\"shiny-plot-output html-fill-item\" id=\"out23706f5c105698a5\" style=\"width:100%;height:400px;\"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n\n## The _t_ distribution\n\nExplore how the shape of the _t_-distribution changes with changes in the degrees of freedom (df). Consider how this change in shape with df affects _P_-values and thus the calculated _t_ values that are considered an indication of statistical significance.\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-4\">\n<form class=\"well\" role=\"complementary\">\n<div class=\"form-group shiny-input-container\">\n<label class=\"control-label\" id=\"df-label\" for=\"df\">Degrees of freedom (df):</label>\n<input class=\"js-range-slider\" id=\"df\" data-skin=\"shiny\" data-min=\"1\" data-max=\"100\" data-from=\"4\" data-step=\"1\" data-grid=\"true\" data-grid-num=\"9.9\" data-grid-snap=\"false\" data-prettify-separator=\",\" data-prettify-enabled=\"true\" data-keyboard=\"true\" data-data-type=\"number\"/>\n</div>\n<div class=\"form-group shiny-input-container\">\n<label class=\"control-label\" id=\"max_t-label\" for=\"max_t\"><p>Maximum of <em>t</em> scale in plot:</p>\n</label>\n<input class=\"js-range-slider\" id=\"max_t\" data-skin=\"shiny\" data-min=\"1\" data-max=\"50\" data-from=\"15\" data-step=\"1\" data-grid=\"true\" data-grid-num=\"9.8\" data-grid-snap=\"false\" data-prettify-separator=\",\" data-prettify-enabled=\"true\" data-keyboard=\"true\" data-data-type=\"number\"/>\n</div>\n<div id=\"tails\" class=\"form-group shiny-input-radiogroup shiny-input-container shiny-input-container-inline\" role=\"radiogroup\" aria-labelledby=\"tails-label\">\n<label class=\"control-label\" id=\"tails-label\" for=\"tails\">Choose tail</label>\n<div class=\"shiny-options-group\">\n<label class=\"radio-inline\">\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"tails\" value=\"right\"/>\n<span>right</span>\n</label>\n<label class=\"radio-inline\">\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"tails\" value=\"left\"/>\n<span>left</span>\n</label>\n<label class=\"radio-inline\">\n<input type=\"radio\" name=\"tails\" value=\"both\" checked=\"checked\"/>\n<span>both</span>\n</label>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>Arrows show quantiles for <em>P</em> = 0.1 (red), 0.01 (orange), 0.001 (green) for the area away from zero.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Remember that the area under the curve as a whole represents <em>P</em> = 1</p>\n\n<p>The dashed line shows the <em>Normal</em> distribution with mean = 0, and s.d. = 1.</p>\n\n</form>\n</div>\n<div class=\"col-sm-8\" role=\"main\">\n<div class=\"shiny-plot-output html-fill-item\" id=\"out0eca73db55a501e7\" style=\"width:100%;height:400px;\"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n\n## The _F_ distribution\n\nExplore how the shape of the _F_-distribution changes with changes in the degrees of freedom (df<sub>1</sub>, df<sub>2</sub>). Consider how this change in shape with df<sub>1</sub> and df<sub>2</sub> affects _P_-values and thus the calculated _F_ values that are considered an indication of statistical significance.\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n```{=html}\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-4\">\n<form class=\"well\" role=\"complementary\">\n<div class=\"form-group shiny-input-container\">\n<label class=\"control-label\" id=\"df1-label\" for=\"df1\">Numerator df:</label>\n<input class=\"js-range-slider\" id=\"df1\" data-skin=\"shiny\" data-min=\"1\" data-max=\"100\" data-from=\"4\" data-step=\"1\" data-grid=\"true\" data-grid-num=\"9.9\" data-grid-snap=\"false\" data-prettify-separator=\",\" data-prettify-enabled=\"true\" data-keyboard=\"true\" data-data-type=\"number\"/>\n</div>\n<div class=\"form-group shiny-input-container\">\n<label class=\"control-label\" id=\"df2-label\" for=\"df2\">Denominator df:</label>\n<input class=\"js-range-slider\" id=\"df2\" data-skin=\"shiny\" data-min=\"1\" data-max=\"100\" data-from=\"10\" data-step=\"1\" data-grid=\"true\" data-grid-num=\"9.9\" data-grid-snap=\"false\" data-prettify-separator=\",\" data-prettify-enabled=\"true\" data-keyboard=\"true\" data-data-type=\"number\"/>\n</div>\n<div class=\"form-group shiny-input-container\">\n<label class=\"control-label\" id=\"max_F-label\" for=\"max_F\"><p>Maximum value of <em>F</em> in the plot axis:</p>\n</label>\n<input class=\"js-range-slider\" id=\"max_F\" data-skin=\"shiny\" data-min=\"1\" data-max=\"50\" data-from=\"15\" data-step=\"1\" data-grid=\"true\" data-grid-num=\"9.8\" data-grid-snap=\"false\" data-prettify-separator=\",\" data-prettify-enabled=\"true\" data-keyboard=\"true\" data-data-type=\"number\"/>\n</div>\n<p>Arrows show quantiles for <em>P</em> = 0.1 (red), 0.01 (orange), 0.001 (green) for the area to its right.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Remember that the area under the curve as a whole represents <em>P</em> = 1</p>\n\n</form>\n</div>\n<div class=\"col-sm-8\" role=\"main\">\n<div class=\"shiny-plot-output html-fill-item\" id=\"out6c86594337ced79f\" style=\"width:100%;height:400px;\"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n```\n:::\n:::\n\n\n::: coallout-note\nHow did I make these interactive displays?\n\nThis Quarto HTML page is made interactive using Shiny, an R package. The viewers of the presentation can change the assumptions underlying what's presented and see the results immediately. \n\nTo learn more, see [Interactive Documents](http://rmarkdown.rstudio.com/authoring_shiny.html).\n:::\n",
